        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Split Fiction developer Hazelight celebrates 50 million games sales, but it's not its newest game that dominates the pie chart]]></title>
            <link>https://www.eurogamer.net/split-fiction-developer-hazelight-celebrates-50-million-units-sold</link>
            <guid>1485640</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>
      <article data-ads="true" data-article-type="news" data-article-group="news" data-paywalled="false" data-premium="false" data-sponsored="false" data-type="article">


<header data-component="article-header">
  

    <div id="main-content">
        

        <p>"Your love and support keeps us going."</p>

    </div>


  <p>

  <figure>
      <picture>
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/split-fiction-mio-and-zoe-and-dragons.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 1dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/split-fiction-mio-and-zoe-and-dragons.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.5&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 1.5dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/split-fiction-mio-and-zoe-and-dragons.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.75&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 1.75dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/split-fiction-mio-and-zoe-and-dragons.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 2dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/split-fiction-mio-and-zoe-and-dragons.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=3&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 3dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/split-fiction-mio-and-zoe-and-dragons.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 1dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/split-fiction-mio-and-zoe-and-dragons.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.5&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 1.5dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/split-fiction-mio-and-zoe-and-dragons.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.75&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 1.75dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/split-fiction-mio-and-zoe-and-dragons.jpg?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 2dppx)">
        
      </picture>

        <figcaption>
          <span>Image credit: <cite>Hazelight Studios</cite></span>
        </figcaption>
  </figure>
  </p>

    

</header>
  <div data-component="article-content">


            <p>Hazelight Studios - the developer behind local co-op delights <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/a-way-out">A Way Out</a>, It Takes Two, and <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/split-fiction">Split Fiction</a> - has announced it has passed a surprisingly large sales milestone: more than 50 million sales.</p>
<p>Arguably the biggest surprise comes in the breakdown of how many copies each game has sold, though. It's not last year's <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/split-fiction-review">Split Fiction, a success by all accounts</a>, that dominates the list with 7m sales, nor is it 2018's A Way Out - the company's first game - with 13m sales. Rather, it's 2021's <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/it-takes-two">It Takes Two</a>, with a gigantic 30m sales.</p>
<p>To put that success in comparison, <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/pokemon-scarlet-and-violet-review-the-ambition-is-betrayed-by-the-performance">Pokémon Scarlet &amp; Violet</a> sits at roughly 28m copies sold, and our 2022 Game of the Year, <a href="https://www.gematsu.com/2025/04/elden-ring-shipments-and-digital-sales-top-30-million">Elden Ring, crossed 30m copies sold last year.</a></p>
<p>It's worth noting these numbers don't include <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/brothers-a-tale-of-two-sons">Brothers: A Tale of Two Sons</a>, which was directed by Josef Fares but developed at Starbreeze Studios before Hazelight came to be. <a href="https://www.hazelight.se/games/">The company's site</a> currently has it listed as part of its portfolio since many of its staff worked on it.</p><figure>
<p>
<a aria-label="It Takes Two - Official “We’re Better Together” Trailer" data-platform="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/QyQYWjX8ufw?autoplay=1" onclick="((e) => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.closest('.video_wrapper').innerHTML = e.currentTarget.querySelector('template').innerHTML; enableElements(); })(event)" title="Click to play video from YouTube">
<span>It Takes Two - Official “We’re Better Together” Trailer</span>
<template>
<iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen="" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/QyQYWjX8ufw?autoplay=1" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/QyQYWjX8ufw?autoplay=1" title="It Takes Two - Official “We’re Better Together” Trailer">
</iframe> </template>
</a>
</p>
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QyQYWjX8ufw" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figure>
<p>"Your love and support keeps us going and we can't wait to show you our fourth game," <a href="https://x.com/HazelightGames/status/2041820156607742336">Hazelight said on X.</a> <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/hazelight-next-new-game-in-development">The studio announced that it was working a new game earlier this year</a>, and though we know nothing yet about it, I expect it will feature co-op heavily.</p>

        </div>

  
      </article>



  



